  abstract2    = {The design of traction mechanism and load-carrier of continuous conveying units (e. g. plastic chains) based so far on a purely mechanical dimensioning. However, mechanical limits are only limited applicable to avoid system failure. With higher speeds or pressures, especially the thermal stress increases, which results in system failure based on softening or melting of the materials at a certain temperature. By means of systematic studies correlations between the friction temperature, the coefficient of friction, the wear and process parameters are determined. On this basis, limits are determined and a model for calculating the friction temperature is developed.}
